\subsection{Model}
% Was the model written out correctly?
% Were any greek letters used clearly defined?

To analyze this data we used a Gaussian process, which is a finite collection of random variables that follow a multivariate normal distribution, as shown below in equation \ref{modeq}. Each of the terms in the model are also explicitly defined below. 

\begin{equation}
  \Y \sim \mathbf{N} ( \X \boldsymbol{\beta} , \sigma^{2} \mathbf{R} )
\label{modeq}
\end{equation}


\begin{align*}
    \Y &= \text{response vector} \quad (nx1)\\
    \mathbf{X} &= \text{model matrix} \quad (nxp)\\
    \boldsymbol{\beta} &= \text{model coefficients} \quad (px1)\\
    \sigma^{2} &= \text{variance term} \quad (scalar) \\
    \mathbf{R} &= \text{structure of covariance matrix} \quad (nxn)
\end{align*}

The guassian proccess model allows for data that is correlated in the response. 
